HEADWORD: Phonation
<hw>Pho*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>fwnh`</grk> the voice.]</ety> <def>The act or process by which
articulate sounds are uttered; the utterance of articulate sounds;
articulate speech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

